edients</span></div><div class="ingredients" itemprop="recipeIngredient"><div class="ingredient">250g&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2276">Lean tuna</a></div><div class="ingredient">2 tablespoons&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2176">White sesame seeds</a></div><div class="ingredient">1 teaspoon&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2277">Black sesame seeds</a></div><div class="ingredient">2 cloves&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2216">Garlic</a></div><div class="ingredient">2 or more tablespoons&nbsp;<a class="product-link" href="/en/ingredients/2178">KOMBU TSUYU</a></div><div class="ingredient">3 teaspoons&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2175">Vegetable oil</a></div><div class="group-head">Side</div><div class="ingredient">30g&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2278">Watercress</a></div><div class="ingredient">1/4 pcs&nbsp;<a class="" href="/en/ingredients/2198">Onion</a></div></div><div class="product-information"><ul class="products"><li class="product-box"><a class="cs" href="http://www.yamasa.com/english/products/retail/seasoning-retail/kombu-tsuyu-retail/"><div class="image"><img src="https://recipe.yamasa.com/rails/active_storage/representations/redirect/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbTNmIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ce602e24a58139c71574ff39fdc296980505df0e/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaDdCem9MWm05eWJXRjBTU0lJY0c1bkJqb0dSVlE2RkhKbGMybDZaVjkwYjE5c2FXMXBkRnNIYVFMZ0FXa0NhQUU9IiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJ2YXJpYXRpb24ifX0=--8944f4592aa464c0d9c5a21d9c2947d9d77f579f/a7deb0aede1d1d3335a6bcc605b5fc8f.png?locale=en" /></div><div class="words words-en"><div class="head-word">This recipe uses</div> <div class="main-word">KOMBU TSUYU</div>
</div></a></li></ul></div><div class="visible-xs"><h2>PREPARATION</h2><ol class="instructions" itemprop="recipeCuisine"><li>Tear watercress into pieces using hands. Slice onion thin. Refresh both watercress and onion in cold water and drain. Slice garlic.</li><li>Coat tuna with <a class="product-link" href="http://www.yamasa.com/english/products/retail/seasoning-retail/kombu-tsuyu-retail/">&quot;KOMBU TSUYU&quot;</a> (2 tablespoons) and vegetable oil (2 teaspoons), and refrigerate for 10 minutes.</li><li>Mix white and black sesame seeds on a tray and spread them out. Cover the tuna refrigerated in STEP2 with the sesame seeds in a tray.</li><li>Put the sliced garlic from STEP1 and vegetable oil (1 teaspoon) to a frying pan over medium heat. When you smell the garlic cooking, add STEP3 and sauté. Cook for 1 minute on each side. Place the tuna on a cutting board. Wait for 1-2 minutes, and cut into proper size. Dish up with garlic and vegetables as a side, and dress with <a class="product-link" href="http://www.yamasa.com/english/products/retail/seasoning-retail/kombu-tsuyu-retail/">&quot;KOMBU TSUYU&quot;</a>.</li></ol></div></div><div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-8"><div class="recipe-search visible-xs"><h3 class="title">OTHER RECIPES THAT MAY INTEREST YOU</h3><div class="product-recipe-list"><ul id="related-recipe-slider"></ul></div><div class="visible-xs"><h3 class="title">MOST POPULAR</h3><div class="product-recipe"><ul id="ranking-recipe-slider"><li><div class="product-recipe-photo"><a href="/en/recipes/1453"><img src="https://recipe.yamasa.com/rails/active_storage/representations/redirect/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb2h2IiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--be22a4e240a376e5c27c0fabb85682c95d26b7ae/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaDdCem9MWm05eWJXRjBTU0lJYW5CbkJqb0dSVlE2RkhKbGMybDZaVjkwYjE5c2FXMXBkRnNIYVFMZ0FXa0NhQUU9IiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJ2YXJpYXRpb24ifX0=--6feffee7c65eecfcf3c859a4c2158773ad0e829f/1453.jpg?locale=en" /></a></div><div class="product-reci